President Obama has appointed Daniel Werfel as the Acting Commissioner of Internal Revenue. Werfel will be responsible for implementing new safeguards to restore public trust and ensure fair and honest administration of the tax code. He has experience working in both Democratic and Republican administrations and is known for his professionalism, integrity, and skill. Werfel currently serves as the Controller of the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) and has led efforts to improve program integrity across the federal government. He has received national and local awards for his contributions to federal financial management and holds degrees from Duke University, the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill, and Cornell University.